Another large-scale combined missile and drone attack was carried out on Ukraine last night. Targets were hit in Ivano-Frankivsk, Kyiv, Khmelnytskyi, Donetsk, Kirovohrad, and Mykolaiv Oblasts.
The following was used:
~8 Kh-101 cruise missiles launched from 1 Tu-95MS and 1 Tu-160 strategic bomber over the village of Uzmore, Saratov Oblast.
~10 Kalibr cruise missiles launched from 2 Buyan-M class corvettes off the coast of Gelendzhik, Krasnodar Krai, in the eastern Black Sea.
250+ Geran-2 drones launched from several launch points surrounding Ukraine. 
Interception rates are unknown, but 5 Kh-101s and likely all 10 Kalibrs impacted their targets. 
As for the targets, information is still being clarified, but I can confirm the following was hit:
Kation Plant in Khmelnytskyi City, Khmelnytskyi Oblast by ~3 Kh-101 cruise missiles.
Kalush Industrial Hub in Kalush, Ivano-Frankivsk Oblast by ~7 Kalibr and ~2 Kh-101 cruise missiles.
An unknown target in northwestern Kyiv Oblast by ~3 Kh-101 cruise missiles.
Lutsk, Volyn Oblast by 25+ Geran-2 drones.
Lviv City, Lviv Oblast by 20+ Geran-2 drones.
Nizhyn, Chernihiv Oblast by 14+ Geran-2 drones.
Rivne City, Rivne Oblast by 12+ Geran-2 drones.
Berezivka, Odesa Oblast by 10+ Geran-2 drones.
Znamyanka Locomotive Depot in Znam'yanka, Kirovohrad Oblast by 6+ Geran-2 drones.
Dobropilska Mine in Dobrobpillya, Donetsk Oblast by 6+ Geran-2 drones.
Surroundings of Zhytomyr City, Zhytomyr Oblast by 6+ Geran-2 drones. 
Vyshhorod/Hostomel/Bucha, Kyiv Oblast by 6+ Geran-2 drones.
Novodonetske, Donetsk Oblast by 3+ Geran-2 drones.
Large fires are now burning in Khmelnytskyi. At least one of the missiles hit a garage cooperative (media 2).

NASA FIRMS data shows that a large fire is burning at the Kation construction plant in Khmelnytskyi after it was hit by ~3 Kh-101 cruise missiles. 
This plant has been used for ammunition storage in the past, although to my knowledge no secondary detonations have been reported.

NASA FIRMS data shows that large fires are burning in Znamyanka, Kirovohrad Oblast, after it was hit by at least 6 Geran-2 drones during last night's strikes. 
The targets were the locomotive depot and the train station. Ukrzaliznytsia announced widespread train delays in numerous regions due to "damage to railway infrastructure". 
Locomotive depot: 48.713482, 32.663084
Railway station: 48.710409, 32.704414
